    "content_hash": "53a81de9ee4f4423",
    "department": "Community",
    "description": "About Cantina Labs:\n\nCantina Labs is a social AI company, developing a suite of advanced real-time models that push the boundaries of expression, personality, and realism. We bring characters to life, transforming how people tell stories, connect, and create. We build and power ecosystems. Cantina, our flagship social AI platform, is just the beginning.\n\nIf you're excited about the potential AI has to shape human creativity and social interactions, join us in building the future.\n\nAbout the Role:\n\nWe’re looking for Community Ambassadors to help support, host, and guide creators and users as Cantina continues to grow.\n\nAs a Community Ambassador, you support and elevate the Cantina experience by hosting live rooms, guiding creators through workflows, and ensuring users can engage meaningfully with the product. You play an important role in helping creators get started, answering questions in real time, and contributing to a welcoming, high-quality community environment.\n\nThis is a camera-on, mic-on role that requires comfort with live hosting, moderation, and active participation in live rooms. This is a 3-month contract role to start, with the potential to extend based on performance, availability, and evolving program needs. For this hiring round, we’re prioritizing candidates who can reliably support weekend shifts; additional weekday availability is a plus.\n\nWhat You'll Do:\n\nHost and facilitate live rooms\n\n - Host Cantina-owned rooms\n\n - Be microphone-ready and comfortable appearing on camera\n\n - Help guide the flow, tone, and engagement of live experiences\n\n - Treat each shift as an opportunity to support a high-quality, consistent experience\n\nSupport creators and users\n\n - Help creators onboard, build AI bots, and understand Cantina’s tools and workflows\n\n - Answer questions clearly and confidently in real time\n\n - Support creators in progressing through key moments on the platform\n\n - Assist creators participating in Cantina programs such as the Creator Fund and Residency\n\nMaintain product fluency\n\n - Build familiarity with Cantina’s features, tools, and workflows\n\n - Stay up to date on new launches, updates, and changes\n\n - Explore and test the product regularly to better support users\n\n - Surface feedback, bugs, and recurring questions to internal teams\n\nModerate and uphold community standards\n\n - Foster a welcoming, inclusive, and respectful environment\n\n - Help uphold Cantina’s Community Guidelines and Terms of Service\n\n - De-escalate conflicts and escalate issues through established internal channels when needed\n\nContribute to community growth\n\n - Support events, programming, and community initiatives\n\n - Collaborate with Community and Marketing teams on engagement efforts\n\n - Stay informed on trends, internet culture, and creator behavior relevant to the platform\n\nWeekly expectations\n\n - Support scheduled shifts reliably and communicate availability clearly\n\n - Complete assigned weekly deliverables related to hosting, creator support, or feedback gathering\n\n - Track time and availability using Cantina tools\n\nWhat You'll Bring:\n\n - Comfortable hosting live on camera and microphone\n\n - Experience with live or social platforms such as Twitch, TikTok Live, Discord, or similar\n\n - Strong communicator with a friendly, approachable presence\n\n - Curious about AI, social platforms, and emerging creator tools\n\n - Able to work independently while collaborating with a distributed team\n\n - Organized and thoughtful about time management and boundaries\n\n - Able to reliably support weekend shifts; weekday availability is a plus\n\nNice to Have:\n\n - Experience moderating online communities or live chat rooms\n\n - Familiarity with AI or creative tools\n\n - Experience creating content or engaging audiences on social media\n\n - Experience supporting creators or users on fast-evolving platforms\n\nContract Details:\n\n - Rate: $20/hour\n\n - Hours: 15–40 hours per week\n\n - Term: Initial 3-month contract, with potential for extension\n\n - Availability: This role is primarily focused on weekend coverage (Saturday - Sunday), with nice-to-have availability during the week as needed\n\n - Location: Remote\n\n - Equipment: Must have access to a reliable laptop and mobile device",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
